RACE.FOOTNOTES: NORGAY away without apparent mishap, was the outermost of three contending for the top, mostly from the three path, began to shake free of the others during the late stages of the run around the bend, was in the vicinity of the three-sixteenths pole when asked for more, responded and steadily kicked clear. ACHILLES HEEL was put to a firm hold shortly after the field had been sent on its way, kept watch on the dispute a little up ahead, two to three wide, saw the pilot resort to a drive a few strides past the the half mile pole, stayed within striking distance, stepped into the stretch and continued its pursuit in earnest, checked when bumped into by an errant AFJAN with approximately a sixteenth to go, recovered with good courage and won the place. AFJAN set up towards the two path after the start, was in between rivals vying for the command until late on the turn, came under stronger handling right around the five-sixteenths marker, was shaken off, came out twice, the second time after some left side stick work, bumped into the runner up, went on to lose out on second to that one. LEGENDARY LORE three wide onto the turn, swung out one path wider exiting it, failed to get involved. CLASH A. J. a bit sluggish on the chute, dove onto the inside route by its conclusion, went on to save ground to no avail. OPEN TIL MIDNIGHT bobbled soon after the start, displayed no ill effects and moved up into a forward position, showed the way on a narrow advantage, feeling pressure from a pair of opponents to the outside, ventured onward under same scenario until the general area of the five-sixteenths marker, came under a drive at that station, fell back, then fell back even more in the lane. There was a General Stewards' Inquiry focusing on the incident in deep stretch before the result was allowed to stand and the race was declared official.
